{"#pw":{"uri":"#pw","http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type":[{"uri":"http://rdfs.org/sioc/ns#WikiArticle"}],"http://purl.org/dc/terms/title":["pw"],"http://rdfs.org/sioc/ns#wikiText":[{"http://rdfs.org/sioc/ns#content":"<p>&#13;\n<a href=\"README\">HOWTO install</a><br />&#13;\n<a href=\"ruby/\">source code</a>&#13;\n</p>&#13;\n<p><b>pw</b> is inspired by classic Apache/HTTPD \"serve files off the filesystem\" designs, only now with a request-time metadata-model to support transcoding arbitrary in-and-output MIMEs. this is handled by <a href=\"https://github.com/ruby-rdf\">RDF Graphs</a> and our <a href=\"http://src.whats-your.name/pw/ruby/graph.rb.html\">JSON/Hash</a> format designed for speed, built on native JSON-handling</p>&#13;\n&#13;\n<p>to allow disparate clients, server-behavior conforms to <a href=\"https://github.com/linkeddata/SoLiD\">SoLiD</a> and <a href=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/ldp/\">LDP</a> conventions. it is a goal to enable everything from <a href=\"https://github.com/linkeddata\">advanced JS UIs</a> to primitive HTML browsers like <a href=\"http://lynx.isc.org/\">lynx</a> and <a href=\"http://links.twibright.com/\">links</a></p>&#13;\n&#13;\n<p>&#13;\nsome usages are reading/archiving <a href=\"conf/mail/\">mail</a> <a href=\"http://m.whats-your.name/today/\">(example),</a> aggregating <a href=\"conf/news/\">news/posts</a> <a href=\"http://b.whats-your.name/news/\">(example),</a> running discussion-boards/<a href=\"ruby/message.rb.html\">forums</a>&#13;\n or just reading a <a href=\"http://man.whats-your.name/ruby\">man page</a></p>","datatype":"html"}],"http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label":["doc"],"http://rdfs.org/sioc/ns#has_creator":[{"uri":"https://carmen.rww.io/profile/card#me"}],"http://purl.org/dc/terms/date":["2015-05-15T09:20:51+00:00"],"http://www.w3.org/ns/posix/stat#mtime":[1431681651]}}